# Azure DevOps MCP Server

Use the Azure DevOps MCP Server (@azure-devops/mcp) to interact with Azure DevOps via natural language. Version: 2.5.0.

## Quick Start

### Local Server (Recommended)
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "azure-devops": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@azure-devops/mcp@2.5.0", "YOUR_ORG_NAME"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Remote Server (Preview)
```json
{
  "servers": {
    "ado-remote": {
      "url": "https://mcp.dev.azure.com/{organization}",
      "type": "http"
    }
  }
}
```

## Authentication

**Local server**: Uses Azure CLI credentials or PAT
```bash
az login
# OR set environment variable
export ADO_MCP_AUTH_TOKEN="your-personal-access-token"
```

**Remote server**: Uses Microsoft Entra ID (OAuth)

## Available Toolsets

| Toolset | Tools Prefix | Description |
|---------|--------------|-------------|
| `repos` | `repo_*` | Repositories, branches, pull requests |
| `wit` | `wit_*` | Work items, backlogs, queries |
| `pipelines` | `pipelines_*` | Builds, runs, artifacts |
| `wiki` | `wiki_*` | Wiki pages, content |
| `work` | `work_*` | Iterations, team capacity |
| `testplan` | `testplan_*` | Test plans, suites, cases |
| `search` | `search_*` | Code, wiki, work item search |

### Filter by Toolset
```json
{
  "args": ["-y", "@azure-devops/mcp@2.5.0", "MY_ORG", "-d", "repos,wit,pipelines"]
}
```

Or via headers (remote):
```json
{
  "headers": {
    "X-MCP-Toolsets": "repos,wiki,wit"
  }
}
```

